2026-01-11T13:22:18.6045822Z options:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6046046Z   -h, --help            show this help message and exit
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6046391Z   -v, --version         Show program version info and exit.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6046788Z   --distpath DIR        Where to put the bundled app (default: ./dist)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6047256Z   --workpath WORKPATH   Where to put all the temporary work files, .log, .pyz
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6047658Z                         and etc. (default: ./build)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6047976Z   -y, --noconfirm       Replace output directory (default:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6048327Z                         SPECPATH/dist/SPECNAME) without asking for
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6048624Z                         confirmation
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6048961Z   --upx-dir UPX_DIR     Path to UPX utility (default: search the execution
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6049323Z                         path)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6049622Z   --clean               Clean PyInstaller cache and remove temporary files
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6049966Z                         before building.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6050323Z   --log-level LEVEL     Amount of detail in build-time console messages. LEVEL
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6050758Z                         may be one of TRACE, DEBUG, INFO, WARN, DEPRECATION,
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6051276Z                         ERROR, FATAL (default: INFO). Also settable via and
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6051650Z                         overrides the PYI_LOG_LEVEL environment variable.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6051887Z 
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6051967Z What to generate:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6052244Z   -D, --onedir          Create a one-folder bundle containing an executable
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6052603Z                         (default)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6052893Z   -F, --onefile         Create a one-file bundled executable.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6053303Z   --specpath DIR        Folder to store the generated spec file (default:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6053704Z                         current directory)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6054045Z   -n NAME, --name NAME  Name to assign to the bundled app and spec file
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6054407Z                         (default: first script's basename)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6054698Z   --contents-directory CONTENTS_DIRECTORY
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6055016Z                         For onedir builds only, specify the name of the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6055484Z                         directory in which all supporting files (i.e.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6055831Z                         everything except the executable itself) will be
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6056176Z                         placed in. Use "." to re-enable old onedir layout
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6056487Z                         without contents directory.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6056670Z 
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6056762Z What to bundle, where to search:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6056989Z   --add-data SOURCE:DEST
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6057266Z                         Additional data files or directories containing data
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6057627Z                         files to be added to the application. The argument
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6057985Z                         value should be in form of "source:dest_dir", where
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6058330Z                         source is the path to file (or directory) to be
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6058671Z                         collected, dest_dir is the destination directory
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6059026Z                         relative to the top-level application directory, and
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6059391Z                         both paths are separated by a colon (:). To put a file
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6059758Z                         in the top-level application directory, use . as a
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6060106Z                         dest_dir. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6060407Z   --add-binary SOURCE:DEST
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6060685Z                         Additional binary files to be added to the executable.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6061198Z                         See the ``--add-data`` option for the format. This
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6061521Z                         option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6061893Z   -p DIR, --paths DIR   A path to search for imports (like using PYTHONPATH).
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6062310Z                         Multiple paths are allowed, separated by ``':'``, or
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6062668Z                         use this option multiple times. Equivalent to
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6063019Z                         supplying the ``pathex`` argument in the spec file.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6063396Z   --hidden-import MODULENAME, --hiddenimport MODULENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6063766Z                         Name an import not visible in the code of the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6064127Z                         script(s). This option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6064444Z   --collect-submodules MODULENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6064754Z                         Collect all submodules from the specified package or
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6065112Z                         module. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6065574Z   --collect-data MODULENAME, --collect-datas MODULENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6065928Z                         Collect all data from the specified package or module.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6066397Z                         This option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6066688Z   --collect-binaries MODULENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6066963Z                         Collect all binaries from the specified package or
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6067318Z                         module. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6067612Z   --collect-all MODULENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6067887Z                         Collect all submodules, data files, and binaries from
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6068260Z                         the specified package or module. This option can be
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6068569Z                         used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6068831Z   --copy-metadata PACKAGENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6069109Z                         Copy metadata for the specified package. This option
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6069433Z                         can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6069705Z   --recursive-copy-metadata PACKAGENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6070017Z                         Copy metadata for the specified package and all its
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6070383Z                         dependencies. This option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6070706Z   --additional-hooks-dir HOOKSPATH
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6070999Z                         An additional path to search for hooks. This option
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6071310Z                         can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6071575Z   --runtime-hook RUNTIME_HOOKS
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6071850Z                         Path to a custom runtime hook file. A runtime hook is
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6072207Z                         code that is bundled with the executable and is
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6072553Z                         executed before any other code or module to set up
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6072899Z                         special features of the runtime environment. This
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6073225Z                         option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6073510Z   --exclude-module EXCLUDES
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6073779Z                         Optional module or package (the Python name, not the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6074150Z                         path name) that will be ignored (as though it was not
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6074500Z                         found). This option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6074891Z   --splash IMAGE_FILE   (EXPERIMENTAL) Add an splash screen with the image
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6075559Z                         IMAGE_FILE to the application. The splash screen can
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6075922Z                         display progress updates while unpacking.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6076132Z 
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6076335Z How to generate:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6076672Z   -d {all,imports,bootloader,noarchive}, --debug {all,imports,bootloader,noarchive}
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6077113Z                         Provide assistance with debugging a frozen
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6077459Z                         application. This argument may be provided multiple
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6077820Z                         times to select several of the following options.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6078103Z                         
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6078345Z                         - all: All three of the following options.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6078622Z                         
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6078875Z                         - imports: specify the -v option to the underlying
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6079233Z                           Python interpreter, causing it to print a message
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6079577Z                           each time a module is initialized, showing the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6079937Z                           place (filename or built-in module) from which it
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6080243Z                           is loaded. See
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6080549Z                           https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#id4.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6080842Z                         
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6081092Z                         - bootloader: tell the bootloader to issue progress
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6081551Z                           messages while initializing and starting the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6081884Z                           bundled app. Used to diagnose problems with
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6082172Z                           missing imports.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6082398Z                         
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6082645Z                         - noarchive: instead of storing all frozen Python
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6082982Z                           source files as an archive inside the resulting
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6083341Z                           executable, store them as files in the resulting
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6083644Z                           output directory.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6083875Z                         
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6084185Z   --optimize LEVEL      Bytecode optimization level used for collected python
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6084602Z                         modules and scripts. For details, see the section
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6085376Z                         “Bytecode Optimization Level” in PyInstaller manual.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6086077Z   --python-option PYTHON_OPTION
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6086546Z                         Specify a command-line option to pass to the Python
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6087134Z                         interpreter at runtime. Currently supports "v"
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6087735Z                         (equivalent to "--debug imports"), "u", "W <warning
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6088320Z                         control>", "X <xoption>", and "hash_seed=<value>". For
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6088875Z                         details, see the section "Specifying Python
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6089409Z                         Interpreter Options" in PyInstaller manual.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6090079Z   -s, --strip           Apply a symbol-table strip to the executable and
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6090782Z                         shared libs (not recommended for Windows)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6091442Z   --noupx               Do not use UPX even if it is available (works
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6092060Z                         differently between Windows and *nix)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6092797Z   --upx-exclude FILE    Prevent a binary from being compressed when using upx.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6093607Z                         This is typically used if upx corrupts certain
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6094304Z                         binaries during compression. FILE is the filename of
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6094987Z                         the binary without path. This option can be used
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6095768Z                         multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6096070Z 
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6096468Z Windows and macOS specific options:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6096766Z   -c, --console, --nowindowed
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6097069Z                         Open a console window for standard i/o (default). On
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6097451Z                         Windows this option has no effect if the first script
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6097777Z                         is a '.pyw' file.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6098023Z   -w, --windowed, --noconsole
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6098316Z                         Windows and macOS: do not provide a console window for
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6098691Z                         standard i/o. On macOS this also triggers building a
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6099049Z                         macOS .app bundle. On Windows this option is
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6099393Z                         automatically set if the first script is a '.pyw'
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6099736Z                         file. This option is ignored on *NIX systems.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6100141Z   --hide-console {hide-late,minimize-late,hide-early,minimize-early}
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6100546Z                         Windows only: in console-enabled executable, have
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6100914Z                         bootloader automatically hide or minimize the console
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6101279Z                         window if the program owns the console window (i.e.,
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6101760Z                         was not launched from an existing console window).
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6102306Z   -i <FILE.ico or FILE.exe,ID or FILE.icns or Image or "NONE">, --icon <FILE.ico or FILE.exe,ID or FILE.icns or Image or "NONE">
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6102846Z                         FILE.ico: apply the icon to a Windows executable.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6103194Z                         FILE.exe,ID: extract the icon with ID from an exe.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6103548Z                         FILE.icns: apply the icon to the .app bundle on macOS.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6103918Z                         If an image file is entered that isn't in the platform
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6104274Z                         format (ico on Windows, icns on Mac), PyInstaller
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6104615Z                         tries to use Pillow to translate the icon into the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6104974Z                         correct format (if Pillow is installed). Use "NONE" to
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6105655Z                         not apply any icon, thereby making the OS show some
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6106014Z                         default (default: apply PyInstaller's icon). This
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6106337Z                         option can be used multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6106624Z   --disable-windowed-traceback
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6106908Z                         Disable traceback dump of unhandled exception in
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6107259Z                         windowed (noconsole) mode (Windows and macOS only),
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6107612Z                         and instead display a message that this feature is
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6107905Z                         disabled.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6108056Z 
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6108139Z Windows specific options:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6108428Z   --version-file FILE   Add a version resource from FILE to the exe.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6108755Z   --manifest <FILE or XML>
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6108993Z                         Add manifest FILE or XML to the exe.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6109314Z   -m <FILE or XML>      Deprecated shorthand for --manifest.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6109615Z   -r RESOURCE, --resource RESOURCE
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6109905Z                         Add or update a resource to a Windows executable. The
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6110236Z                         RESOURCE is one to four items,
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6110549Z                         FILE[,TYPE[,NAME[,LANGUAGE]]]. FILE can be a data file
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6110909Z                         or an exe/dll. For data files, at least TYPE and NAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6111260Z                         must be specified. LANGUAGE defaults to 0 or may be
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6111739Z                         specified as wildcard * to update all resources of the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6112116Z                         given TYPE and NAME. For exe/dll files, all resources
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6112455Z                         from FILE will be added/updated to the final
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6112802Z                         executable if TYPE, NAME and LANGUAGE are omitted or
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6113152Z                         specified as wildcard *. This option can be used
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6113447Z                         multiple times.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6113770Z   --uac-admin           Using this option creates a Manifest that will request
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6114131Z                         elevation upon application start.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6114494Z   --uac-uiaccess        Using this option allows an elevated application to
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6114846Z                         work with Remote Desktop.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6115029Z 
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6115111Z macOS specific options:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6115652Z   --argv-emulation      Enable argv emulation for macOS app bundles. If
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6116039Z                         enabled, the initial open document/URL event is
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6116400Z                         processed by the bootloader and the passed file paths
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6116869Z                         or URLs are appended to sys.argv.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6117158Z   --osx-bundle-identifier BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6117461Z                         macOS .app bundle identifier is used as the default
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6117818Z                         unique program name for code signing purposes. The
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6118168Z                         usual form is a hierarchical name in reverse DNS
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6118469Z                         notation. For example:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6118775Z                         com.mycompany.department.appname (default: first
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6119085Z                         script's basename)
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6119358Z   --target-architecture ARCH, --target-arch ARCH
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6119687Z                         Target architecture (macOS only; valid values: x86_64,
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6120040Z                         arm64, universal2). Enables switching between
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6120377Z                         universal2 and single-arch version of frozen
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6120727Z                         application (provided python installation supports the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6121102Z                         target architecture). If not target architecture is
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6121449Z                         not specified, the current running architecture is
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6121746Z                         targeted.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6121972Z   --codesign-identity IDENTITY
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6122258Z                         Code signing identity (macOS only). Use the provided
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6122618Z                         identity to sign collected binaries and generated
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6122997Z                         executable. If signing identity is not provided, ad-
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6123335Z                         hoc signing is performed instead.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6123610Z   --osx-entitlements-file FILENAME
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6123913Z                         Entitlements file to use when code-signing the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6124226Z                         collected binaries (macOS only).
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6124416Z 
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6124501Z Rarely used special options:
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6124719Z   --runtime-tmpdir PATH
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6124968Z                         Where to extract libraries and support files in
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6125426Z                         `onefile` mode. If this option is given, the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6125751Z                         bootloader will ignore any temp-folder location
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6126100Z                         defined by the run-time OS. The ``_MEIxxxxxx``-folder
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6126581Z                         will be created here. Please use this option only if
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6126937Z                         you know what you are doing. Note that on POSIX
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6127281Z                         systems, PyInstaller's bootloader does NOT perform
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6127633Z                         shell-style environment variable expansion on the
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6127979Z                         given path string. Therefore, using environment
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6128324Z                         variables (e.g., ``~`` or ``$HOME``) in path will NOT
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6128620Z                         work.
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6128835Z   --bootloader-ignore-signals
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6129106Z                         Tell the bootloader to ignore signals rather than
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6129447Z                         forwarding them to the child process. Useful in
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6129790Z                         situations where for example a supervisor process
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6130151Z                         signals both the bootloader and the child (e.g., via a
2026-01-11T13:22:18.6130514Z                         process group) to avoid signalling the child twice.
